	<h1 class="heading-xlarge">Forms</h1>


  <!-- introduction -->
  <div class="text">
  
    <p>Keep forms as simple as possible.</p>
    
    
    <h2 class="heading-medium">Looking for the HTML?</h2>
    
    <p>The HTML snippets can be found in the <a href="/elements/snippets/#forms">snippets page</a>.</p>
    
    
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Form examples</h3>
    
    <ul class="list-bullet">
      <li><a href="your-details/">Your details</a></li>
      <li><a href="where-should-we-send-your-new-passport/">Where should we send your new passport?</a></li>
      <li><a href="register-for-rural-payments/">Register for Rural Payments</a></li>
      <li><a href="form-validation/">Form validation</a></li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Optional and mandatory fields</h3>
    
    <ul class="list-bullet">
      <li>only ask for the information you absolutely need</li>
      <li>if you do ask for optional information, mark the labels of optional fields with '(optional)'</li>
      <li>don't mark mandatory fields with asterisks</li>
    </ul>
  
  </div>


  <!-- labels -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Labels</h3>
  
  
  <ul class="list-bullet text">
    <li>all form fields should be given labels</li>
    <li>don't hide labels, unless the surrounding context makes them unnecessary</li>
    <li>labels should be aligned above their fields</li>
    <li>label text should be short, direct and in sentence case</li>
    <li>avoid colons at the end of labels</li>
    <li>labels should be associated with form fields using the <b>for</b> attribute</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p>Click on the label 'Full name' to bring focus to the form field.</p>
  
  
  <div class="example">
    
    <form class="form">
      
      <label for="full-name">
        <span class="form-label">Full name</span>
      </label>
      
      <input class="form-control" id="full-name" type="text">
      
    </form>
    
  </div>


  <!-- spacing -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Spacing between form elements</h3>
  
  
  <div class="text">
    
    <p>Ensure there is sufficient spacing between form elements.</p>
    
    <p>Use '.form-group' to create spacing when wrapping label and input pairs.</p>
  
  </div>
  
  
  <div class="example">
    
    <form class="form">
      
      <div class="form-group">
        
        <label for="first-name">
          <span class="form-label">First name</span>
        </label>
        
        <input class="form-control" id="first-name" type="text">
        
      </div>
      
      <div class="form-group">
        
        <label for="last-name">
          <span class="form-label">Last name</span>
        </label>
        
        <input class="form-control" id="last-name" type="text">
        
      </div>
      
    </form>
    
  </div>


  <!-- hint text -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Hint text</h3>
  
  
  <ul class="list-bullet text">
    <li>don't use placeholder text in form fields, as this will disappear once content is entered into the form field</li>
    <li>use hint text for supporting contextual help, this will always be shown</li>
    <li>hint text should sit above a form field</li>
    <li>ensure hint text can be read correctly by screen readers</li>
  </ul>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
      <label for="ni-number">
        <span class="form-label">National Insurance number</span>
        <span class="form-hint">It'll be on your last payslip. For example, JH 21 90 0A.</span>
      </label>
      
      <input class="form-control" id="ni-number" type="text">
    
    </form>
  
  </div>


  <!-- dates -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Dates</h3>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
      <fieldset>
      
        <legend>
          <span class="form-label-bold">Date of birth</span>
        </legend>
        
        <div class="form-date">
        
          <p class="form-hint">For example, 31 3 1980</p>
          
          <div class="form-group form-group-day">
            <label for="dob-day">Day</label>
            <input class="form-control" id="dob-day" type="number" pattern="[0-9]*" min="0" max="31">
          </div>
          
          <div class="form-group form-group-month">
            <label for="dob-month">Month</label>
            <input class="form-control" id="dob-month" type="number" pattern="[0-9]*" min="0" max="12">
          </div>
          
          <div class="form-group form-group-year">
            <label for="dob-year">Year</label>
            <input class="form-control" id="dob-year" type="number" pattern="[0-9]*" min="0" max="2014">
          </div>
        
        </div>
      
      </fieldset>
    
    </form>
  
  </div>


  <!-- selects -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Drop&ndash;down lists</h3>
  
  
  <div class="text">
  
    <p>It's advisable to avoid using drop&ndash;lists (the HTML select element) and use radio buttons or checkboxes instead.</p>
    
    <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CUkMCQR4TpY" rel="external">Watch Alice Bartlett present the failings of select boxes to meet the needs of less technically capable users</a>.</p>
    
  </div>
  
  
  <div class="example">
    
    <form class="form">
      
      <label for="legal-status">
        <span class="form-label">Legal status</span>
      </label>
      
      <select class="form-control-select" id="legal-status">
        <option>-- Please make a selection --</option>
        <option value="1">Charitable Interest Organisation</option>
        <option value="2">Community Interest Company</option>
        <option value="3">Government (Central)</option>
        <option value="4">Government Limited Liability Partnership</option>
      </select>
    </form>
    
  </div>


  <!-- search -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Search</h3>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
    <fieldset>
    
      <legend>
        <span class="form-label-bold">What are you looking for?</span>
      </legend>
      
      <div class="form-search">
      
        <div class="form-group-search">
          <input class="form-control" id="search" type="text">
        </div>
        
        <div class="form-group-button">
          <button class="button" type="button">Search</button>
        </div>
      
      </div>
    
    </fieldset>
    
    </form>
  
  </div>


  <!-- textarea -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Textarea</h3>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
      
      <label for="enquiry">
        <span class="form-label">Enquiry</span>
      </label>
      
      <textarea class="form-control form-control-textarea" id="enquiry" rows="6" cols="50"></textarea>
      
    </form>
  
  </div>


  <!-- radio buttons -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Radio buttons</h3>
  
  
  <ul class="list-bullet text">
    <li>use these to let users choose a single option from a list</li>
    <li>for more than two options, radio buttons should be stacked</li>
    <li>radio buttons with large hit areas are easier to select with a mouse or touch devices</li>
  </ul>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
      <fieldset class="inline">
      
        <legend>
          <span class="form-label">Do you know their National Insurance number?</span>
        </legend>
        
        <div class="form-group form-group-compound">
        
          <label class="block-label" for="radio-inline-1">
            <input id="radio-inline-1" name="radio-inline-group" value="Yes" type="radio"> Yes
          </label>
          
          <label class="block-label" for="radio-inline-2">
            <input id="radio-inline-2" name="radio-inline-group" value="No" type="radio"> No
          </label>
        
        </div>
      
      </fieldset>
    
    </form>
  
  </div>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
      <label class="block-label" for="radio-1">
        <input id="radio-1" name="radio-group" value="Northern Ireland" type="radio">
        Northern Ireland
      </label>
      
      <label class="block-label" for="radio-2">
        <input id="radio-2" name="radio-group" value="Isle of Man or the Channel Islands" type="radio">
        Isle of Man or the Channel Islands
      </label>
      
      <p class="form-block">or</p>
      
      <label class="block-label" for="radio-3">
        <input id="radio-3" name="radio-group" value="I am a British citizen living abroad" type="radio">
        I am a British citizen living abroad
      </label>
    
    </form>
  
  </div>


  <!-- checkboxes -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Checkboxes</h3>
  
  
  <ul class="list-bullet text">
    <li>use these to select either on/off toggles or multiple selections</li>
    <li>make it clear with words when users can select one or multiple options</li>
  </ul>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
      <fieldset>
      
        <legend>
          <span class="form-label-bold">Which types of waste do you transport regularly?</span>
        </legend>
        
        <p>Select all that apply</p>
        
        <label class="block-label" for="checkbox-1">
          <input id="checkbox-1" value="waste-animal" type="checkbox">
          Waste from animal carcasses
        </label>
        
        <label class="block-label" for="checkbox-2">
          <input id="checkbox-2" value="waste-mines" type="checkbox">
          Waste from mines or quarries
        </label>
        
        <label class="block-label" for="checkbox-3">
          <input id="checkbox-3" value="farm-agricultural" type="checkbox">
          Farm or agricultural waste
        </label>
      
      </fieldset>
    
    </form>
  
  </div>


  <!-- alternative -->
  <ul class="list-bullet">
    <li>large hit areas aren't always appropriate</li>
    <li>only pre&ndash;select optons if there's a strong, user&ndash;centred reason to</li>
  </ul>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
      <label for="telephone-number">
        <span class="form-label">Enter your telephone number</span>
      </label>
      
      <input class="form-control" id="telephone-number" type="text">
      
      <label class="form-checkbox" for="checkbox-telephone-number">
        <input id="checkbox-telephone-number" value="checkbox-telephone-number" type="checkbox"> I need to be contacted using a text phone
      </label>
    
    </form>
  
  </div>


  <!-- inset elements -->
  <h3 class="heading-medium">Inset form elements</h3>
  
  
  <div class="text">
    
    <p>Insets can be used within forms to emphasise supporting information.</p>
  
    <p>Click on 'Yes' to see how this works.</p>
    
  </div>
  
  
  <div class="example">
  
    <form class="form">
    
      <fieldset class="inline">
      
        <legend>
          <span class="form-label">Do you know their National Insurance number?</span>
        </legend>
        
        <div class="form-group form-group-compound">
        
          <label class="block-label" data-target="example-ni-number" for="radio-indent-1">
            <input id="radio-indent-1" name="radio-indent-group" value="Yes" type="radio">
            Yes
          </label>
          
          <label class="block-label" for="radio-indent-2">
            <input id="radio-indent-2" name="radio-indent-group" value="No" type="radio">
            No
          </label>
        
        </div>
        
        <div class="panel-indent js-hidden" id="example-ni-number">
          
          <label for="national-insurance">
            <span class="form-label">National Insurance number</span>
          </label>
          
          <input class="form-control" id="national-insurance" type="text">
          
        </div>
      
      </fieldset>
    
    </form>
  
  </div>


